---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import { site } from '@data/site';
import { Icon } from 'astro-icon/components';

const title = `Privacy Policy | ${site.hero.name}`;
const description = 'The legal stuff.';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.endsWith('/')
  ? import.meta.env.BASE_URL
  : `${import.meta.env.BASE_URL}/`;
const homeHref = base;
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <p class="mb-8">
    <a
      href={homeHref}
      class="group flex items-center gap-2 text-sm text-accent transition hover:text-slate-light"
      data-astro-prefetch
    >
      <Icon name="ph:arrow-left" class="h-4 w-4 transition-transform group-hover:-translate-x-1" />
      {site.hero.name}
    </a>
  </p>

  <h1 class="mb-8 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-4xl">Privacy Policy</h1>
  <p class="mb-8">
    I do not collect or store any personal information about you. This website does not use cookies or any other tracking technologies to collect information about you. I do not use analytics or any other tools to monitor user behavior or collect data about you. Since the website does not collect any user information, I have no user information to share with or sell to third parties.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-8">
    If you engage with the dark mode switch, the site will use local storage to store your preference and your first click of the switch on your device. This allows your theme preference to persist every time you return to the site. The switch click data is stored to prevent the site from serving the privacy pop up after you've already seen it once. As this is local storage, I can't(therefore don't) collect any information from this. If you wish to remove this after interacting with the switch, click here. By default, the website attempts to set the theme based on your system theme preferences.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-8">
    If you have any questions or concerns about any of this, please feel free to contact me at <a href="mailto:dev@siekmang.com">dev@siekmang.com</a>.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-8">
    In short, some things get saved to your device's local storage, but nowhere else.
  </p>
  <Footer></Footer>
</Layout>
